RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Maiden Special Weight Purse 36000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 123 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUT OF PROMISES was unhurried while along the inside through the turn, guided into the four path approaching the eighth pole then finished with good energy to be clear late. HEAVEN AND EARTH vied for the lead three wide through the turn and into the lane, shook clear into the lane, remained clear with an eighth to go then could not hold the winner safe. PAT'S PALACE raced in the three path through the turn when never far back, continued in the five path for the drive and finished evenly. HURRICANE LASSIE vied for the lead along the inside through the turn and into the lane then weakened along the rail. NO JOKING MATTER vied for the lead through the turn while in between rivals then weakened through the stretch. TEAKETTLE was never a factor while in the three path through the turn. SPOTTY SHOWERS was close early then steadily faded while off the inside. GIRL IN THE CITY vied for the early lead while near the inside, settled off into the turn then was empty entering the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Out of Promises
ENTRY.OWNER: Spooky Hollow Racing Inc. and Hewett, Robert
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, inside turn, guided 4path, drove past

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Spooky Hollow Racing, Inc. & Robert Hewett

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ECLIPSED vied for the lead from the outset, continued with a short lead into the lane, lost the advantage outside the eighth pole then inched up late to prevail. SOFIA STRONG vied for the lead two wide through the turn and into the lane, gained a short lead with an eighth to go then could not hold the winner safe in a game effort. KEEN ICE SIGHT saved ground through the turn while never far back, came off the rail and into the three or four path through the lane and finished with good energy. GO STORMIN GIRL chased the two rival duel through the turn and into the lane then weakened. SENTIMENTALJOURNEY raced in the four to the three path through the turn and never factored. POLYESTER BRIDE showed little while near the inside. KANFU chased the pace from the four path through the turn, was well placed into the lane from the four or five path then faltered.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAPPYKIYAY vied for the early lead while in the two path, shook clear into the turn, widened into the lane then held. CABIN ABBY pressed the pace along the inside into the turn, chased the winner into the lane then weakened inside the eighth pole. DARNELL was never a threat while along the inside. GOLDEN HEIST was in the five to the four path through the turn and into the lane and could not offer a stretch respponse. SEMINOLE MIDNIGHT vied for the early lead while in the three path, chased the winner into the turn then was done near the five-sixteenths pole.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 38500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS SIRED BY REGISTERED INDIANA STALLIONS MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GENTLEMAN LOGAN vied for the early lead while in the three path, cleared on the turn, widened to the eighth pole, looked to be a sure winner with a sixteenth to go, shortened stride late and just lasted. DOUBLEDOGJUSTICE was steadied soon after the start when losing his path, settled back, moved to chase the pace through the turn while in the three or four path, came into the lane from the four path or five path and finished with good energy. STANDOUTJUSTICE was in the three path through the turn when unhurried, came into the lane from the four or five path and was methodically gaining to the end. BIG CITY HEAT chased the pace from the two path through the turn, had aim on the leader after straightening in the lane and just needed more. BUMPY pressed the pace along the inside to the turn, settled back to chase the pace into the lane, was well placed inside the eighth pole but could not gain and lost positions late. OUTSTANDINGJUSTICE was quick early then settled back along the inside and offered a mild gain on the tiring leader. JUST A NOTION was never a threat from off the inside. PURSUANT never a factor while in the three path. BLAME IT ON MILLER never a menace while saving ground. WHOSPACKINMYLUNCH trailed throughout while along the inside. AN OBJECTION FROM THE RIDER OF #9 DOUBLEDOJUSTICE AGAINST THE RIDER OF #10 GENTLEMAN LOGAN FOR INTERFERENCE AT THE START OF THE RACED WAS DISALLOWED.
